# Collaboration & Decision Protocol

- Canonical note: `docs/90-Meta/collaboration-and-decision-protocol.md`. This
  rule is an orchestrator; if it disagrees with that note, the vault wins.
- **Nico = Projektleitung / Lead Architect** — decides architecture, scope,
  technology, gameplay and priorities, and is the only authority that ratifies
  decisions. Agents **support** shaping, research and elaboration (research,
  game-loop analysis, game/engine design, technical analysis) and produce vault
  notes and proposals, never unilateral decisions.
- **Current phase: research / analysis / architecture planning — no
  development.** Do not implement code or create premature versions until Nico
  changes the phase. Decisions are currently reopened (see
  `docs/00-Index/Current-State.md`).
- **Ask-first gate:** before any decision on technology, gameplay, architecture,
  data model, module boundaries, public APIs/contracts, scope, or
  security/privacy — stop, present 2–3 options with sourced best-practice
  rationale + a recommendation, and wait for Nico. This is the FMX expression of
  the stop conditions in `docs/30-Implementation/agent-workflow-pattern.md`.
- **Never shorten a path because it is faster or easier** — thoroughness before
  speed; development does not stop once an MVP exists.
- Research is grounded (Perplexity/Ref/Web) and filed in the vault; see
  `docs/90-Meta/mcp-memory-integration.md`.
